WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.264 --> 00:00:01.180
DAN ATKINS: All right.

00:00:01.180 --> 00:00:03.310
Hi, everybody.

00:00:03.310 --> 00:00:07.440
Thank you for joining us today
for a panel we're calling

00:00:07.440 --> 00:00:09.420
The Reality of Virtual Reality.

00:00:09.420 --> 00:00:10.170
We like the title.

00:00:10.170 --> 00:00:12.870
It sounds dramatic.

00:00:12.870 --> 00:00:13.950
My name is Dan Atkins.

00:00:13.950 --> 00:00:16.800
I'm a publishing
producer here at Google,

00:00:16.800 --> 00:00:20.550
focused on Daydream, which
for us is a combination

00:00:20.550 --> 00:00:22.590
of both our AR and VR efforts.

00:00:22.590 --> 00:00:25.930
But today we're going
to be talking about VR.

00:00:25.930 --> 00:00:28.950
And VR, as you guys know, is
still very much an emergent

00:00:28.950 --> 00:00:29.950
medium.

00:00:29.950 --> 00:00:32.189
It's one where we're
continuing to learn

00:00:32.189 --> 00:00:34.462
from every product
that comes out.

00:00:34.462 --> 00:00:36.420
And more importantly,
we're still in this phase

00:00:36.420 --> 00:00:38.850
where app developers can still
learn a tremendous amount

00:00:38.850 --> 00:00:41.640
from game developers,
and vise versa.

00:00:41.640 --> 00:00:45.030
So we're lucky enough today
to be joined by two people who

00:00:45.030 --> 00:00:50.910
really run the spectrum of VR
entertainment in the industry

00:00:50.910 --> 00:00:53.790
right now and have been
pretty prolific in doing so,

00:00:53.790 --> 00:00:55.500
both having shipped
multiple titles

00:00:55.500 --> 00:00:57.812
across multiple platforms.

00:00:57.812 --> 00:01:00.270
So Nic, Jonathan, thank you
guys so much for being with us.

00:01:00.270 --> 00:01:01.420
JONATHAN FLESHER: Thank
you for having us.

00:01:01.420 --> 00:01:02.710
DAN ATKINS: Yeah, absolutely.

00:01:02.710 --> 00:01:04.500
I'm hoping that
we can start just

00:01:04.500 --> 00:01:07.875
by hearing a little bit
about who you guys are

00:01:07.875 --> 00:01:10.500
and what brought you to VR, and
a little bit about the products

00:01:10.500 --> 00:01:11.461
you've been working on.

00:01:11.461 --> 00:01:12.960
So Nic, maybe we
can start with you.

00:01:12.960 --> 00:01:13.918
NIC VASCONCELLOS: Sure.

00:01:13.918 --> 00:01:15.870
My name is Nic Vasconcellos.

00:01:15.870 --> 00:01:18.270
I am one of the founders
of Turbo Button.

00:01:18.270 --> 00:01:21.150
We are a small
indie studio in LA.

00:01:21.150 --> 00:01:24.930
We are three people strong
and just recently released

00:01:24.930 --> 00:01:28.320
this game, "Along Together"
on Google Daydream.

00:01:28.320 --> 00:01:31.080
And the game is--

00:01:31.080 --> 00:01:33.297
you play as a kid's
imaginary friend,

00:01:33.297 --> 00:01:34.380
going on these adventures.

00:01:34.380 --> 00:01:38.310
And you have the power to
move things in the environment

00:01:38.310 --> 00:01:42.270
and help this kid
find their lost dog.

00:01:42.270 --> 00:01:45.120
So we've been going for
a couple of years now.

00:01:45.120 --> 00:01:47.850
We started in the
beginning of 2015.

00:01:47.850 --> 00:01:51.450
Started by doing a
couple of Gear VR games,

00:01:51.450 --> 00:01:54.620
and then this is our latest.

00:01:54.620 --> 00:01:56.350
DAN ATKINS: Awesome.

00:01:56.350 --> 00:01:57.050
And Jonathan.

00:01:57.050 --> 00:01:58.995
Do you want to do the same?

00:01:58.995 --> 00:02:00.620
JONATHAN FLESHER:
I'm Jonathan Flesher.

00:02:00.620 --> 00:02:03.490
I work at a company
called Baobab Studios.

00:02:03.490 --> 00:02:05.510
It was founded by
Maureen Fan, who

00:02:05.510 --> 00:02:09.440
used to run the "Farmville"
franchises at Zinga.

00:02:09.440 --> 00:02:12.200
And Eric Darnell, who
was the writer/director

00:02:12.200 --> 00:02:14.660
of the "Madagascar" films
when he was at Dreamworks.

00:02:14.660 --> 00:02:16.990
And Larry Cutler,
who is our CTO, who

00:02:16.990 --> 00:02:18.830
was the head of global
character animation

00:02:18.830 --> 00:02:20.105
technology at Dreamworks.

00:02:20.105 --> 00:02:21.480
And so we've really
come together

00:02:21.480 --> 00:02:25.640
as bringing traditional
cinematic animation

00:02:25.640 --> 00:02:28.850
and video game talent
to create something

00:02:28.850 --> 00:02:30.800
new for virtual reality.

00:02:30.800 --> 00:02:33.990
And you'll see on the screen,
we have three pieces today.

00:02:33.990 --> 00:02:35.630
The first one, "Invasion!"

00:02:35.630 --> 00:02:37.252
most recently won an Emmy award.

00:02:37.252 --> 00:02:38.960
We're very flattered
to have that happen.

00:02:38.960 --> 00:02:42.380
And it's been a top performing
app across all the platforms.

00:02:42.380 --> 00:02:45.380
"Asteroids!" will be
released this holiday season

00:02:45.380 --> 00:02:46.880
on Daydream.

00:02:46.880 --> 00:02:50.807
And "Rainbow Crow" will be
coming out sometime next year.

00:02:50.807 --> 00:02:51.640
DAN ATKINS: Awesome.

00:02:51.640 --> 00:02:54.190
And I think we have a
clip to watch on that one.

00:02:54.190 --> 00:02:55.650
JONATHAN FLESHER:
On "Asteroids!"

00:02:55.650 --> 00:02:56.430
DAN ATKINS: On "Asteroids!"

00:02:56.430 --> 00:02:56.700
JONATHAN FLESHER: Yes.

